        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 6:52PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 652 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pine Hall, or near Walnut Cove, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Madison...
Walnut Cove...
Pine Hall...
Dillard...
Ellisboro...
Stokesdale...
and Belews Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
